Subject: [PATCH 02/10] F-04/F-06/F-08/F-09: sanitize module + hardened state
 manager
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

shared/sanitize.js (new):
- esc() HTML-escaper; global window.esc for template literals.

shared/app-state.js v1.9.0:
- Canonical field names: deployed (migrates deployedCapital),
  transactions (merges legacy transactionHistory, time-sorted). (F-09)
- normalizeState(): numeric coercion, guaranteed arrays, monotonic
  nextLoanId/nextMemberNumber derived from max existing IDs. (F-09)
- recalculateDerivedTotals(): deployed and memberFundsHeld computed
  from records on every load; hand-kept counters no longer drift. (F-06)
- getNextLoanId(): collision-free ID reservation. (F-09)
- importJSON(): the single sanctioned restore path — size ceiling,
  shape check, normalization, full validate() with readable errors;
  validate() now catches duplicate IDs, negative balances, bad terms,
  non-finite money fields. (F-08)
- load() preserves an unreadable blob under a .corrupt key instead of
  silently discarding the ledger; verbose logs behind DEBUG. (F-17)
